On Tue, 29 Jul 2003, Mac Norton wrote:

> Tim has identified the problems, including what may be the most important
> one, that the "market," unlike other such markets, is subject to gaming
> for motives that are other than economic.

Actually this is the fundamental failure of your view, Tim's, and most
other CACL sorts.

ALL markets are subject to parameters that are -not- subject to strictly
economic motives. In fact a purely 'economic motive' isn't fundamentally
about money, it's about either insecurity or power, it's about
inter-personal relationships. It's about 'using'.


